            <thetext>When the index.html cannot load the initial loader script (e.g. &quot;custom.js&quot;), 
there is not error message, no feedback, nothing that tells the user the load 
failed. He is simply presented with an empty browser window.

Similarily, when loads to subsequent .js files fail, nothing is logged or 
alerted. Only when a required class is missing, a sensible error message is 
shown.

It would be very helpful, both for app and core developers, if these error 
situations could be made obvious.</thetext>
